UID:5503a1419510bb55@gid-seminars.wnprc.wisc.edu
CATEGORIES:WHO
DESCRIPTION:An outbreak of Ebola virus disease caused by the Bundibugyo vi
 rus was declared on 15 May 2026 in the Democratic Republic of the Congo (D
 RC)\, with cross-border spread to Uganda. The World Health Organization ha
 s classified the event as a Public Health Emergency of International Conce
 rn due to its severity and potential for international spread. This webina
 r will explain why this outbreak is significant\, WHO recommendations and 
 the rationale behind them.\n\nEvent URL: https://www.who.int/news-room/eve
 nts/detail/2026/06/09/default-calendar/who-health-emergencies-epi-win-webi
 nar-ebola-bundibugyo-virus-disease-what-we-know\n\nSource: who_events
